their weekly debate demand.Labour headquarters indicated instead that their leader would take part in two head-to-head debates against Mr Sunak, matching what Boris Johnson and Jeremy Corbyn did before the 2019 election.What channels are the debates on?The BBC, ITV and Sky News have hosted election debates in an array of formats.All broadcasts from the BBC are available on BBC1, BBC News and are live on the corporation‚Äôs streaming platform BBC Iplayer. It is also airing some debates on local radio.The ITV leaders‚Äô debate is available on its steaming service ITVX.Each platform has also streamed programmes on YouTube.The Telegraph is providing live coverage of all the debates with expert analysis and reaction.Will the debates clash with any football fixtures?There have been several clashes between debate timings and football fixtures ‚Äì an inevitability with the jam-packed TV schedules.Football fans and politics watchers were torn on June 7, when the BBC‚Äôs debate with the seven parties coincided with England‚Äôs international warm-up with Iceland on Channel 4.England played Denmark the same day as the BBC‚Äôs Question Time special, but an earlier kick-off time of 5pm meant the match had finished before the election programme at 8pm.Who won the previous debates?June 4, ITV leaders‚Äô debateMr Sunak seemed¬†extraordinarily confident and¬†put in¬†one of the best performances seen in an election debate, Janet Daley said.Tom Harris, conversely, held that Sir Keir Starmer¬†made more of the opportunity, effectively skewering the Prime Minister on his party‚Äôs record in government.June 7, BBC leaders‚Äô debateSherelle Jacobs held that Nigel Farage made real inroads in his bid to overtake the Tories as the preferred party of the Right.But Tom Harris was not convinced, saying that¬†Stephen Flynn, Westminster leader of the SNP, and Plaid Cymru leader Rhun ap Iorwerth¬†fared best.June 12,¬†Sky News‚Äôs The Battle for Number 10Tim Stanley said the public came out worse fro